## Bombable Walls and Bomb Holes

### Closed Bombable Walls

A configured bombable wall appears visually identical to an ordinary wall in Zelda 1.

Bombing the wall:

1. consumes one bomb,
2. opens the passage,
3. updates `CurOpenedDoors`,
4. and preserves the opened passage when leaving and returning.

A north bombable wall changed:

```text
CurOpenedDoors: $00 → $08
```

### Initial Opened State

The door-type attribute describes what kind of doorway exists.

`CurOpenedDoors` describes whether that doorway is currently open.

These properties can be configured separately.

For example:

```text
Door type: Bombable
Starts open: No
```

creates a normal wall that must be bombed.

```text
Door type: Bombable
Starts open: Yes
```

creates an already-open bomb passage.

### Opened-Door Bits

| Side  |   Bit |
| ----- | ----: |
| East  | `$01` |
| West  | `$02` |
| South | `$04` |
| North | `$08` |

All four sides set together produce `$0F`.

### Four-Side Confirmation

All four sides were configured as bombable and initialized as open.

All four bomb holes rendered and behaved as open passages immediately after room loading.

This confirms that starting-open state can be applied independently across the complete doorway bit field.
